Organization: Department of Computer Science, University of Edinburgh
Lines: 24

BCPL stands for "Butchered Computer Programming Language", and was developed by
Martin Richards of the Computer Laboratory, Cambridge University, UK. The
development history of these languages is:

   CPL --> BCPL --> B --> C --> C++
             |
             +--> MCPL

As previously stated, AmigaDOS is based on the experimental Tripos operating
system which was used on the CL's first distributed system (the Cambridge Ring
network) which ran on 68000 and Z80 based servers.

Martin Richards still uses his BCPL compiler (the only one there is, AFAIK) to
illustrate his lecture course on compiler design, much to the anguish of his
students! He can be contacted by email at mr@cl.cam.ac.uk

Dave
