No, the 'original inventors' are hardly dead.  Doug still has an
email address as far as I know.  The point is that neither Apple
*nor* Xerox is in a particularly morally-strong position [although
the legal details vary] to be bringing suit over "their" stuff.
Moreover, Doug's stuff was gov't funded and so public-domain.
Hence, there was no question of copying the *real* original stuff.

